List of questions

what does [Arigatou / ありがとう] mean? 

1: sorry 2: thank you 3: good afternoon 4: hello 

what does [Sensei / せんせい] mean? 

1: parents 2: student 3: uncle 4: teacher 

How do you say hello in Japanese? 

1: sayonara 2: konnichiwa 3: ohayo 4: hello 

How many “alphabets” does Japanese have? 

1: 1 2: 2 3: 3 4: 4 

How do you say "Good night" in Japanese? 

1: おはよう (Ohayou) 2:こんばんは (Konbanwa) 3:さようなら (Sayonara) 4: いただきます (Itadakimasu) 

How do you say "Yes" in Japanese? 

1: いいえ (Iie) 2: はい (Hai) 3: こんにちは (Konnichiwa) 4: さようなら (Sayonara) 

How do you say "No" in Japanese? 

1: いいえ (Iie) 2: はい (Hai) 3: こんにちは (Konnichiwa) 4: さようなら (Sayonara) 

How do you ask "What's your name?" in Japanese?  

1: なんですか？ (Nandesuka?) 2: お元気ですか？ (Ogenki desu ka?) 3: 何ですか？ (Nani desu ka?) 4: お名前は何ですか？ (Onamae wa nan desu ka?) 

What is the Japanese word for "water"?  

1: ねこ (Neko) 2: いぬ (Inu) 3: みず (Mizu) 4: たこ (Tako) 

Translate "花" (Hana) into English.  

1: Flower 2: Sun 3: Rain 4: Tree 
Translate the phrase "お誕生日おめでとうございます" (Otanjobi omedetou gozaimasu) into English.  

1: Happy birthday 2: Congratulations 3: Thank you very much 4: Excuse me 

How do you say "I don't understand" in Japanese?  

1: わかります (Wakarimasu) 2: わかりません (Wakarimasen) 3: すみません (Sumimasen) 4: ありがとう (Arigatou) 
what does [Tomodachi / ともだち] mean? 

1: friend 2: dog 3: tomorrow 4. Saturday 

what does [Kanpai / かんぱい] mean? 

1: food 2: dinner 3: cheers 4: good luck 
